def: One who animadverts; a censurer; also [Obs.], a chastiser.
The common tern; -- called also tarret, and tarrock. [Prov.Eng.]
A harmless North American snake of the genus Heterodon, esp. H.platyrhynos; -- called also puffing adder, blowing adder, and sandviper.
The female of the domestic fowl; also, the female of grouse,pheasants, or any kind of birds; as, the heath hen; the gray hen.
Of a size less than is common.
The state of being a son, or of bearing the relation of a son;filiation. Dr. H. More.
The conveyance of a soul from one body to another. [R.] Fuller.
One of the writers of the Masora.
Dividing into cells or segments; characterized by separationinto two or more parts or sections by the formation of internalpartitions; as, merismatic growth, where one cell divides into many.
The coarse-grained brownish yellow wood of a small tree(Pisonia obtusata) of Florida and the West Indies. Also called pigeonwood, beefwood, and corkwood.
